# RecursiveSerendipity - Project Rules

## What This Project Is
RecursiveSerendipity is a local-first autonomous agentic runner that executes evolutionary perfection loops. It generates, tests, critiques, and refines code artifacts recursively until they meet quality thresholds, using local LLMs via Ollama on a 192GB M2 Ultra Mac Studio.

## Architecture
- **Tauri v2 Shell** (Rust + React): Desktop app frame, IPC, process management
- **Bun Engine** (TypeScript): Core logic in `engine/` directory, runs as HTTP server on port 9700
- **LangGraph.js State Machine**: Generator -> BuildChecker -> Evaluator -> Refiner loop
- **Ollama**: Local LLM inference. Primary models: llama3.3 (generator), deepseek-r1:70b (critic)
- **SQLite** (via bun:sqlite): Persistence for runs, variants, checkpoints in `data/rs.db`
- **SSE**: Real-time streaming from engine to Tauri frontend

## Key Directories
- `engine/` - Bun backend (the brain). Run with `bun run engine/index.ts`
- `engine/graph/` - LangGraph state machine, nodes, edges
- `engine/providers/` - Ollama and thermal monitoring
- `engine/execution/` - Child process management, linting, sandboxing
- `engine/memory/` - SQLite persistence
- `engine/heuristics/` - Scoring functions (lint, build, composite)
- `src/` - React frontend components
- `src-tauri/` - Rust backend (Tauri v2)
- `data/` - Runtime data (gitignored)

## Coding Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- No `any` types
- Bun APIs for file/process operations in engine (Bun.spawn, Bun.serve, bun:sqlite)
- LangGraph Annotation.Root for state schema
- React functional components with hooks
- Inline styles with style objects (no CSS-in-JS libraries)
- All LLM calls go through OllamaProvider's queue (sequential heavyweight inference)

## Running
1. Start engine: `bun run engine/index.ts` (or `npm run engine`)
2. Start full app: `npm run tauri dev` (starts Vite + Tauri, engine auto-spawned by Rust backend)
3. Engine health: `curl http://localhost:9700/health`

## Model Strategy
- Sequential heavyweight: One model loaded at a time to maximize quality per inference pass
- OllamaProvider manages a request queue to prevent concurrent model loading
- Thermal monitoring throttles workload under pressure

## Self-Improvement (Phase 3, not yet implemented)
- Engine has `self-improve/` directory for future recursive self-improvement
- Safe zones: heuristic weights, prompt templates, UI components
- Protected zones: core graph logic, persistence layer, IPC

## Important
- NEVER make external API calls. All inference is local via Ollama
- NEVER use Docker or Wasm. Native child_processes only
- Data directory is gitignored. SQLite WAL mode for concurrent reads
- The Tauri Rust backend proxies all frontend requests to the Bun engine via HTTP
